Durban - Private hospital group Mediclinic Southern Africa said on Tuesday that it had acquired a majority stake in Life Path Health.Life Pathis a mental health treatment provider operating seven facilities currently concentrated in the Western Cape, with a further three in the process of development in other regions of South Africa.The acquisition of the majority stake in Life Path Health is subject to the fulfilment of a number of suspensive conditions, including the approval of the transaction by the competition authorities.Read also: Mediclinic earnings hit by Al Noor buyMediclinic Southern Africa chief executive Koert Pretorius said: There is a strong alignment between Life Path Health s current health-care offering and Mediclinic s vision of transforming into a more integrated health-care service provider, offering a broader range of services to our patients. BUSINESS REPORT